name: NPR
text:
As much as 95% of Kaziranga National Park in India may be underwater, following severe rain and flooding.

Now, officials are working to save stranded animals — including the area's rare one-horned rhinos.

The launch of the James Webb Space Telescope — the long-awaited successor to the Hubble Space Telescope — has been pushed back yet another seven months, NASA says.
